From: Tuxbox Builder <noreply@tuxbox.org>
Date: Fri, 20 Dec 2024 14:00:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] samba-common: use bash for postinst script

The pkg_postinst:${BPN}-common:append() function uses bash-specific [[  ]]
test syntax. Change the shebang from #!/bin/sh to #!/bin/bash since bash
is already installed in the image.

Signed-off-by: Tuxbox Builder <noreply@tuxbox.org>
---
 meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/samba/samba-pkgs.inc | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/samba/samba-pkgs.inc b/meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/samba/samba-pkgs.inc
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/samba/samba-pkgs.inc
+++ b/meta-oe/recipes-connectivity/samba/samba-pkgs.inc
@@ -177,7 +177,8 @@ FILES:${PN}-pidl = "${bindir}/pidl ${datadir}/perl5/Parse"

 pkg_postinst:${BPN}-common:append() {
-#!/bin/sh
+#!/bin/bash
+# Using bash because this script uses bash-specific [[ ]] syntax

 set +e
 grep -v 'pam_smbpass.so' $D/etc/pam.d/common-password > $D/tmp/common-password
--
2.34.1
